(2590, 14, 3, 'Atika Ghulamali', 'atika777@hotmail.com', 'mashydary@gmail.com', 'Ask a Question', 'Dear,<br />\nName : Atika Ghulamali<br />\nEmail : atika777@hotmail.com<br />\nAsk Message<br />\nSalam,\n\nJust saw that the homework for Akhlaq and Tareekh show 60 some percent.  I know that Farwa has been doing all her homework.  Wondering if its just not entered.  Please let me know.\n\nAtika Ghulamali', 0, 'Custom Teacher (14)', '2015-02-23 10:32:14', '[]'),
(2591, 26, 3, 'MehdiReza Hirji', 'Mehdicpa1@gmail.com', 'taha.dharsi@gmail.com', 'Ask a Question', 'Dear,<br />\nName : Zehra Hirji<br />\nEmail : mehdicpa1@gmail.com<br />\nAsk Message<br />\nAssalaamun Alaykum Br. Taha,\n\nI wanted to get back to you in regards to the pop quiz that was missing for Ameerah.  The reason you may not have one is due to her absence that day.  I wanted to ask you did this affect her Quran results?  Her absence was acknowledged by the administration and she was proactive in submitting her Homework via her sisters to the teachers but there was no mention of a Quiz .  Had we been informed of the missed quiz,  we would have taken the correct actions to rectify this.   Ameerah also did mention she was quite nervous when doing the recitation exam for Quran.   I would like to know how we can prepare her better, she gets nervous when testing with you,  as well as when she is presented new ayats that she has not been exposed to.    \n\nJazakallah,', 0, 'Custom Teacher (26)', '2015-02-28 11:39:41', '[]'),
(2592, 19, 3, 'Masooma Farishta', 'masooma_zz@hotmail.com', 'sharokh.pournazari@gmail.com', 'Ask a Question', 'Dear,<br />\nName : Masooma Farishta<br />\nEmail : masooma_zz@hotmail.com<br />\nAsk Message<br />\nSalam Br. Sharoukh\nHasnain had a little hard time with his Arabic writing homework. He was able to do 3 pages but it was taking him some time to do each line ( I wanted to make sure he was writing them correctly and not rushing through it just to get it done). I just wanted to ask you if it was ok if he took another week to finish it?\nThank you!\nMasooma', 0, 'Custom Teacher (19)', '2015-03-01 06:11:42', '[]'),
(2593, 117, 4, 'Sister Samena Premjee', 'samena@premjees.com', 'Agokal@bgalawyers.com', 'Heros Project', 'Dear Parents, \n\nSalaamalaykum. This year in Class 2 we will be doing a Hero Project for our final presentation. In our class, we have studied major figures like the 14 Masumeen, Prophet Adam, Prophet Ibrahim, Prophet Nuh, Prophet  Youseef, Prophet Yonus, Prophet Mohammed, Prophet Isa, and the Major Personalities present at Kerbala. For our end of the year project/presentation, I would like each child to pick out who their hero in Islam is. We will be working on this in class as well as at home. We will be presenting this in front of the other classes and parents as well. It will be a short 30 second to 1 minute few sentences. Please see below for a sample:\n\nSalam Alykum, my name is __________ and my hero is _______________.  He/she is my hero because __________________.  I would want to be like her/him because___________.\n\nI will need each child to have their hero picked out and memorized by Sunday March 29, 2015.\n\nWe dont want it to be too long, as there will be other presentations that day. Please send your child in shalwar kameez for the day of presentations. More details will be sent later.\n\nIf you have any questions, please email me at Samena@premjees.com or call me at (949) 331-6259. \n\nThank you,\nSamena Premjee \nClass 2\n', 0, 'All Parents of Class (2)', '2015-03-01 19:58:07', '[]'),
