(2633, 33, 3, 'Brother Taha Dharsi', 'taha.dharsi@gmail.com', 'murtaza.1993@outlook.com', '2nd Semester', 'Salam Alikum wrwb,\n\nInshallah we will start with the new course for the 2nd semester from tomorrow. Please find the new text books attached.\n\nClass 9 & 10 Teachers,\n\nI will be conducting a joint class for Class 9 girls, Class 10 boys & girls and request your assistance with it. I would greatly appreciate towards the following roles & responsibilities towards your respective classes:-\n+ Take attendance\n+ Collect weekly H.W and grade them. (I will provide guidelines)\n+ Control behavioral issues (I cant teach and keep control 29 students all by myself)\n+ Grade Finals ( I will write up the exam and provide grading guidelines)\n+ Any more are TBD \n-------------------------------------------------------\nBelow is a brief course outline for the joint classes for this semester:-\nRules:\n-Weekly H.W reading and summary (from Principles of Faith by Sheikh Wahid)\n-All H.W hand written, clear & readable \n-Take notes in class for your survival\n-If you have questions, write them down and ask them during Q&A \nGoals:\n-Enhance critical thinking \n-We will focus on ''how you get to the answer'' rather than the ''answer''\n-Have gained the knowledge to the path of certainty in ones belief\nRequired Course Texts:-\n1. Class 9 and 10 Aqaid Text book\n2. Principles of Faith by Sheikh Wahid \n---------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nFor the first 2 sessions I will discuss some introductory matters of logic to enhance their critical thinking ability and then we will dive into discussing from the text books.\nI have already attached 2 H.W assignments for the next 2 weeks. Please send them out to the students at your earliest. The H.W.s attached are to be dealt with as follows:-\n1. For  "Critical_Thinking_Concepts_and_Tools.pdf" students are required to read through it and submit pg 11 after having read any article of their choice and submit on 3/15/15.\n2. For "Fallacies.docx" students are required to read through it and submit their own examples of the 15 fallacies described in this handout. This is due on 3/22/15 and you can make this available as soon as this Mon to give them 2 weeks if they wish.\n\nPlease feel free to contact me if you have any questions. I would like to have short meeting tomorrow when you all have a chance to discuss the goals of this semester.\n\nJazakAllah.\nYa Ali.\nMohamed Taha Dharsi', 0, 'Teacher Classroom', '2015-03-07 22:07:05', '[{"file_name":"2015\\/03\\/07\\/Class_6.pdf","file_only":"Class_6.pdf"},{"file_name":"2015\\/03\\/07\\/Class_9_and_10.pdf","file_only":"Class_9_and_10.pdf"},{"file_name":"2015\\/03\\/07\\/Fallacies.docx","file_only":"Fallacies.docx"},{"file_name":"2015\\/03\\/07\\/Critical_Thinking_Concepts_and_Tools.pdf","file_only":"Critical_Thinking_Concepts_and_Tools.pdf"}]'),
