(3029, 12, 3, 'Sumana Kazmi', 'summana.kazmi@gmail.com', 'hiba.raza101@yahoo.com', 'Quran Teacher', 'Salam,\nI sent a letter with Fyza about 3 weeks ago requesting a copy of what she is learning in Quran class (Qaida) with the roman english for pronunciation. i''m not sure if anyone received it. I will follow up after the assembly this week but wanted to check if you had received it or the quran teacher had. \nThank you again for all your wonderful work and dedication to the children''s islamic education.', 1, 'Custom Teacher (12)', '2015-05-06 18:55:45', '[]'),
(3030, 32, 4, 'Sister Hiba Raza & Sister Sukaina Ali', 'hiba.raza101@yahoo.com', 'summana.kazmi@gmail.com', 'Quran Teacher', 'Wassalaam,\n\nIn the last two weeks, the Quran classes have shifted a little due to the change in the students level. I am Fyza''s new Quran teacher for the rest of the year. However, I do remember seeing Fyza give the previous Quran teacher a letter but I never physically saw it. I would be happy to discuss my plan with you for the last 3 weeks this Sunday.\n\nThank you for your dedication as well.\n\n-Hiba Raza', 0, 'Specific Parents', '2015-05-06 19:03:38', '[]'),
(3031, 6, 3, 'Nargis Hasnain', 'nargiswh@yahoo.com', 'masooma_zz@hotmail.com', 'Ask a Question', 'Dear,<br />\nName : Masooma<br />\nEmail : nargiswh@yahoo.com<br />\nAsk Message<br />\nSalam, \n     How are you?  Here is my two questions for the final:\nIf a mosquito lands on you, and you squash it on your clothes, are you still tahir?\nTrue, because the blood that possibly may have been in the mosquito, is part of the mosquito no matter whose kind of blood it was before.\n\nIf your foot is najis, and you wash a najis object in the sink, are you tahir?\nFalse, because you didn''t clean your feet while washing the najis object. \n\nThank you, \nMasooma Hasnain', 1, 'Custom Teacher (6)', '2015-05-07 22:19:29', '[]'),
(3032, 25, 0, 'Brother Reza Busheri', 'rezalution786@gmail.com', '', 'Akhlaq - Final Study Guide', 'The Final for this class will be conducted on May 17th. It will cover all material since the first class (Back-biting  Visiting the Sick), with an emphasis on the second half (Pride and Arrogance - Visiting the Sick).\n\nKey Terms from first-half chapters:\nBack-Biting\nSlander\nMisleriness\nHonesty and Truthfulness\nKindness to Animals\nRespect for Parents\nRespect for Teachers\nImportance of Hijab\nForgiveness\nGenerosity\n\nEmphasis on final:\nPride and Arrogance\nJealousy\nThe Quran\nTrust in Allah [SWT]\nNeighbors\nVisiting the Sick\n\n\nPlease have the students go through the chapters in the book and look over each part (stories, quran sayings, "Did you Know?", "Key Points", making sure they can answer all the summary questions and learning objectives. Also have them go over the two previous quizzes.\n', 0, 'Teacher Classroom', '2015-05-10 15:31:54', '[{"file_name":"2015\\/05\\/10\\/Class_6_\\u2013_Akhlaq_Final_Study_Guide_9388.docx","file_only":"Class_6_\\u2013_Akhlaq_Final_Study_Guide_9388.docx"}]'),
