(3040, 30, 4, 'Nausheen Mithani', 'school@jafaria.org', 'Sajjad@premjees.com', 'Aqaid final Review/from brother murtaza', 'Salam,\n\nAs per our conversation I have mentioned below what we reviewed over in class this last Sunday. The students were told that there will be 20 multiple choice and t/f questions. They were also given 3 essay questions that they should prepare for and what they should mention in their answers but only 2 of the 3 questions will be on the test.\n\nWhy do we need prophets? Why can we not function religiously function without them? (I told the students that they should talk about more in depth how prophets are expert teachers, a reminder, spiritual leaders, an example for us all, and receivers of divine revelations) How do we know that the person claiming to be a prophet is a prophet (through miracles). Pg 19-21\nHow do we know that God is just ( we went over how zulm is the opposite of adalat amd why god doesn''t need to do zulm; also make the separation between gods justice and how its different from equality? Why is god being just an important quality of god? ( students were told to mention how there wont be a qiyamaat or people would not get rewarded or punished accordingly if god wasn''t just and so on). pg 14-17\nThis question is similar to the first one and on imamat and how does this differe from prophethoot? (students were told to discuss how imams are needed to guard the religion whereas prophets expanded and spread it; they are also political leaders, proof of Allahs mercy). How are imams appointed? How do we know a person claiming to be an imam is an imam (miracles). pg. 26-28\n\nAs for the multiple choice questions it students were told they will be based from the whole book and we went over sample questions.\n', 0, 'Specific Parents', '2015-05-11 19:20:10', '[]'),
(3041, 17, 3, 'MehdiReza Hirji', 'Mehdicpa1@gmail.com', 'shussain_raza88@hotmail.com', 'Ask a Question', 'Dear,<br />\nName : Zehra Hirji<br />\nEmail : zaznz@yahoo.com<br />\nAsk Message<br />\nAsalaamun Alaykum Br. Raza,\n\nAs Hunaina and I prepare for the upcoming exam I would like to know if there is a study guide or some guide line as to what will be covered.  She has been a bit vague about what is to be covered.  I am under the impression that everything is up for assessment from the beginning of the year, is this true?  I would really appreciate some idea as to which direction we need to take in studying for this exam.\n\nJazakallah Khair,\nZehra \n\n', 0, 'Custom Teacher (17)', '2015-05-11 20:22:34', '[]'),
